The paper deals with the problem of detecting deep fakes in portrait videos, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.MM). The paper also proposes a novel approach to detecting deep fakes using biological signals, which involves analyzing and classifying data, making it relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the issue of security and privacy, which is related to the sub-category of cryptography (cs.CR).
